[[chapter-introduction]]
== Introducing Hudson

[[intro-sect-intro]]
=== What is Hudson?

Hudson is a powerful and widely used open source continuous
integration server.

=== Continuous Integration

Martin Fowler and Kent Beck are largely credited with the first use of
the term "Continuous Integration" as applied to the software
development with Kent Beck's seminal 1999 book Extreme Programming
Explained being the first published work touching upon the idea of
creating systems to continuously build and test systems in response to
changes in source control.

NOTE: Beck, Kent (1999). Extreme Programming Explained. ISBN
0-201-61641-6.

=== General Purpose Scheduler

