As you can see from the output above a hudson user was created . This
user will run the Hudson server. The Hudson home folder is configured
to be located in +/var/lib/hudson+, which will contain configuration,
workspaces and so on and should be added to your backup strategy.

Step 5: Upgrade Hudson::

  To upgrade Hudson when a new release is available you would run

----
sudo apt-get upgrade
----

which will stop the running Hudson server, upgrade Hudson and restart
the server. Prior to upgrading you might want to backup your Hudson
data configuration located in +/var/lib/hudson+ and owned by the
